## Justice (58, 135)

An-Nisa contains one of the most powerful verses in the Quran on justice:

> *"O you who believe, stand firmly for justice as witnesses to God, even if it be against yourselves, your parents, or your relatives. Whether one is rich or poor, God is more worthy of both."* (135)

Justice isn't something you apply when it's convenient. It applies **even when it costs you**. Even when the guilty party is yourself, your mother, your father, your family. Even when the person you're protecting is your enemy.

Another verse reinforces this:

> *"God commands you to return trusts to their rightful owners, and when you judge between people, to judge with justice."* (58)

